title.narrative: CHILD SENSITIVE SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: National integrated social protection system and other stakeholders provide effective quality continuum of services, and support protective norms and behaviours for children and families with special focus on protection from and prevention of any form of violence, especially child separation, which contributes to Child Protection Systems, Data And Child Protection, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Reduce disparities, increase equity and promote the social inclusion of vulnerable boys and girls.
